Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat. Add turkey and sausage; cook 6 minutes or until browned, stirring to crumble turkey. Remove from pan and keep warm. Add onion, cumin, and crushed red pepper to pan; cook 5 minutes over medium heat or until onion is translucent. Add garlic; cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Return turkey and sausage to pan. Add soy sauce and next 6 ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes. Ladle chili into bowls, and sprinkle evenly with cheese. Serve with green onions and sour cream, if desired.